DIA, Sonae SGPS: Spain, Portugal Equity Preview for Aug. 24

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-08-24T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/dia-sonae-sgps-spain-portugal-equity-preview-for-aug-24.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  fell 0.2 percent to 8,279.8.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  slipped 0.2 percent to 6,094.79.  Spanish stocks:  Distribuidora Internacional de Alimentacion SA (DIA SM):
The Madrid-based discounter named Mariano Martin Mampaso as vice
chairman of the board. The shares dropped 0.2 percent to 2.61
euros.  Portuguese stocks:  Sonae (SON)  SGPS SA: The Portuguese retailer said net
income dropped to 35 million euros in the first half from 41
million euros a year earlier. Sonae said in a filing it expects
growing pressure on sales and margins for the rest of the year.
The shares fell 0.9 percent to 52.6 euro cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
